# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
#           RoboKaty — config.env.sample
#   Copy this to config.env and fill in your values
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# ── REQUIRED ─────────────────────────────────────
# Get from @BotFather
BOT_TOKEN=

# Get from my.telegram.org
API_ID=
API_HASH=

# PostgreSQL connection string
# Format: postgres://user:password@host:5432/dbname
DATABASE_URI=postgres://robokaty:password@localhost:5432/robokatydb

# Telegram channel ID where bot logs go (negative number)
LOG_CHANNEL=

# ── OPTIONAL ─────────────────────────────────────
# Your Telegram user ID (bot owner)
OWNER_ID=

# Space-separated list of sudo user IDs
SUDO=

# Telegram username of support channel (without @)
SUPPORT_CHAT=RoboKaty

# Database name
DATABASE_NAME=RoboKatyDB

# Timezone (for night mode scheduling)
TZ=Asia/Kolkata

# Web server port
PORT=8080

# Command prefixes — space separated
# /start .start !start — all will work
COMMAND_HANDLER=/ . !

# Auto restart on crash (true/false)
AUTO_RESTART=false

# ── AUTO FORWARDER (optional) ─────────────────────
# Space-separated chat IDs to forward FROM
FORWARD_FROM_CHAT_ID=

# Space-separated chat IDs to forward TO
FORWARD_TO_CHAT_ID=

# File types to forward (space-separated)
FORWARD_FILTERS=video document
